Both tests pass and `verify.py` exits 0.

The patch adds an HTTP middleware to `bb009_observe/app.py` that:
- Reads `x-correlation-id` from the incoming request, falling back to a generated `uuid4().hex` when absent or empty.
- Measures duration with `time.perf_counter`.
- Appends a single event dict to `app.state.events` with exactly `method`, `path` (from `request.url.path`, so `/items/42`), `status_code`, `duration_ms`, and `correlation_id` — no headers or bodies, so authorization data never enters the event.
